# TypeScript Types and Enums for Chess WebSocket

All enums, interfaces, and type definitions for the chess WebSocket protocol are centralized in [type.ts](mdc:src/utils/type.ts).

**Key Points:**
- Enums for sides (`SideEnum`), game states (`GameStateEnum`), and WebSocket message types (`WebSocketMessageTypeEnum`).
- Interfaces for all WebSocket messages, including create/join/move/chat/resign/pairing, etc.
- Union types for all possible incoming and outgoing WebSocket messages.
- Local storage keys and types for persisting game details.
- All message types and payloads should match the protocol in [api.md](mdc:docs/api.md).

**Reference:** See [type.ts](mdc:src/utils/type.ts) for the authoritative source of all chess WebSocket types and enums.
